Description:
Modern Living On Myers
This stylish, simple and a spacious townhouse ticks all the boxes, a beautifully designed home that has everything you desire. Situated in the heart of East Geelong, this home boasts low maintenance gardens, excellent entertaining qualities and light filled rooms which can lap up the sun all year round.
On offer are 3 spacious bedrooms, master with full size ensuite and walk in robe, second and third bedrooms are both generous in size and have built in robes, large central bathroom with full size bath and ample lighting, modern and newly renovated kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances, beautiful floorboards. The sun filled, North facing living area is warm and welcoming, taking advantage of the northern sunshine, additional formal living room, laundry and ample storage throughout the home.
Stepping outside we have a North facing backyard perfect for relaxing or entertaining, DLUG with extra width, keyless entry and rear-lane access.
Perfectly ideal for the downsizer, small family, or investment, you too could live an easy distance to East Geelong's Boutique Cafe Precinct, local Schools, public transport, botanic gardens, Geelong Waterfront and the CBD. This property won't last long!

Description:
As Good As It Gets in Booming Newcomb
This charming weatherboard home oozing character is secured on approximately 655sqm of land in the ever-growing market of Newcomb. Eye catching & immaculately presented comprising of 4 bedrooms with BIRs, 2 Bathrooms & 2 car spaces with character to pair, homes alike are few & far between. Matched with an ideal locale within close proximity to both Newcomb Shopping Centres, Bellarine Peninsula within 15 minutes, reputable schools & only a 5-10 minute drive to Geelongs City Centre.
Accompanying the exterior is the well thought out interior, capturing a heritage feel with high ceilings & an open plan feel. The kitchen presents solid timber bench tops, 900mm freestanding stainless steel oven/5 Burner Gas Cook top & rangehood. The two separate bathrooms service the household with the main bathroom offering a shower over bath.
The large outdoor alfresco lined with café blinds presents the perfect entertaining area that overlooks your own oasis with a salt chlorinated, solar heated family pool offering prime opportunities for backyard entertaining. Alongside is the 7.5 x 9m (approx) shed that all of your mates will be envious of with a toilet, sink & wood fire that and a separate room that could be used as a possible fifth bedroom.
Extras Includes:
- Exposed Aggregate Driveway
- 2x Split System (Heating/Cooling)

Description:
Excellent First Home or Investment Opportunity
As the rising popularity of Newcomb continues to build, here is an opportunity to purchase in one of the best pockets of this area, in a continually growing property market. This much loved family home offers you a welcoming abode, generous block of land, close proximity to shopping, parks, amenities, CBD and a fantastic lifestyle of ease and convenience. You will feel an instant sense of homeliness on entering this house, with the main living, adjoining dining and kitchen area located at the front of the home, taking advantage of is orientation toward the north. Large windows bring in plenty of natural light and provide a pleasant outlook to the street. Consisting of three good sized bedrooms, two with BIR, central bathroom and generous backyard, this home would be a great fit for first-home buyers or investors. Set on an impressive 592m2 (approx.) block, this property offers scope to renovate or extend (STCA) and improve its value. Located only a 1 minute walk from the Watsons Road Shopping strip, 5 minutes walk from Bellarine Shopping Centre, easy walking distance from bus routes, schools, Eastern Gardens and less than 3km from the Geelong CBD, this property offers suburban living with all of the conveniences of the inner-city. This is your chance to secure a fantastic property, abundant with potential and situated in a sought after growth location. Offering convenience of proximity to everything you need for an easy and enjoyable lifestyle, this is one you dont want to miss!

Address: 4 Ranken Lane St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
QUIET COURT SPACIOUS LIVING
Set in a private laneway of only 4 properties, on 380m2 approx block, this neat as a pin 3 bed, 2 bath, 2 living property would suit a First Home Buyer, savvy investor with a potential rent of $400 - $420 pw or a downsizer with low maintenance yard and being close to central Geelong.
Offering brand new blinds, carpet and freshly painted this spacious home comprises of master bedroom located at the front of the home and offers WIR and handy ensuite with toilet, corner shower and vanity storage plus heat lamps for those frosty mornings.
There is also a bright formal front lounge room with inverter split system and timber floating floors, making it an ideal room to retreat to and relax.
Stepping into the hub of the home, you will be greeted with a wonderful open plan style living/dining/kitchen area. This room is equipped with an ornate gas log fire, AC wall box for all year round comfort. The dining space easily seats up to 6 and flows nicely off the functional corner kitchen which is equipped with dishwasher and electric cooktop and oven.
Located at the rear of the home are a further 2 spacious bedrooms, all freshly painted and carpeted and offer brand new blockout blinds and ceiling fan.
The central bathroom is bright and offers bath, separate shower, vanity storage and heat lamps.
Outside you will find a neat landscaped rear yard with secure gate, new fencing and a small undercover pergola area ideal for summer BBQ's.
This wonderful start property is ideally located a 5 min drive to Geelong CBD, 15 minutes to the coast and 2km to local cafes, sporting grounds and Buckleys entertainment complex .
FEATURES:
Split system
Ducted Gas heating
2 Living areas
Rent pw $400 - $420

Description:
QUALITY RENOVATED HOME IN GROWTH CORRIDOR
The stylish renovated 4 bed, 1 bath, 2 living room property set on 660m2 would suit an array of buyers. Whether you are a young professional couple, a growing family, or a savvy investor looking for capital growth, this property is a must to inspect.
Being freshly painted inside and offering new carpets and venetian blinds throughout, this home comprises of light filled front lounge room with polished hardwood floors, LED downlights, brand new Braemar gas wall heater and ceiling fan for all year round comfort. The sun drenched kitchen is spacious and offers new vinyl covered cabinetry, brand new oven and range-hood, new dishwasher and ample cupboard space.
Located at the front of the home are 2 spacious bedrooms, master is king size and offers a leafy front garden outlook. Both are equipped with ceiling fans, mirrored built in robes and ample storage.
Located at the rear of the home the third and fourth bedrooms are large in size and are equipped with LED lighting, and mirrored BIR's. They are also connected to the second living/rumpus room which offers ceiling fan, making this an ideal space for kids to play.
The central bathroom is stylishly updated and offers a modern free standing bath, brand new tiling, corner shower and vanity storage, plus heat lamps for those chilly mornings. The spacious laundry and toilet is well positioned behind the bathroom and could easily be converted to become a second bathroom.
What sets this home apart from the rest is the quality finishes and second living room, equipped with matching hardwood flooring, reverse cycle split system and handy access to the side merbau deck or rear atrium courtyard.
Outside you will find a DLUG and workshop which could be changed to house 3-4 cars. There is also ample parking in the driveway to house, campervan, trailer etc.
There is lush rear gardens, a flat back yard perfect for kids or your 4 legged friend. This property is ideally located close to local parks, less than 2km from Geelong CBD, a short 2 minute drive to local schools and Newcomb Shopping Centre and 15 min to the Coast.
660m2 block approx
4 bedrooms

Pick of the Crop!
Situated in a quiet street right in the heart of one of Geelong's premiere suburbs, with botanic gardens and the Geelong waterfront just a short stroll away. Upon entering this home, you will be greeted with high ceilings, decorative archways, polished Baltic pine floors and period light fittings. It's a perfect example of a renovated home, blending both the old-world charm of yesteryear with a modern and stylish open plan.
This home offers a spacious modern kitchen including stainless steel appliances, ample storage and a walk-in pantry, large open living and dining featuring polished timber floors and access to deck and separate courtyards, the master bedroom in enormous and light filled, including large walk in robe and beautifully appointed ensuite, three double bedrooms (two with built in robes), a separate study, a modern family bathroom and separate laundry.
Other features include; decorative cornices and period features throughout, evaporate cooling and central heating, security system, enclosed carport with remote control access, manicured gardens, garden shed, north facing deck with retractable awning.
This is a unique opportunity to secure a property in this location, only a block from the East Geelong boutique shopping precinct, great schools and public transport.

Description:
Immaculate Home in Prized Location
Set in one of East Geelongs most picturesque and sought-after pockets, this immaculately presented home will appeal to all buyers. The stunning façade has been reinvigorated in a modern colour scheme which perfectly accentuates the homes beautiful character features and combined with modern fittings and finishes makes this property the perfect opportunity to enter the East Geelong market.
On entry the classic wide central hall reveals three generous sized bedrooms that are light and spacious featuring ornate fireplaces that enhance the character of the home. All bedrooms are well serviced by the central bathroom which has been completely updated.
The cozy living room is light and bright with large windows and glass doors, fireplace, mantle and flows perfectly into the open dining and kitchen space. The updated kitchen provides a modern workspace with quality appliances, subway tiles and timber lined walls which blend perfectly with the style of the home.
Moving into the backyard, the undercover deck and second entertaining area is situated with convenient access from the dining room through two sets of double doors. Remote rear lane access through a roller door allows for ample off-street parking and a large shed could easily be converted for further parking or a great storage.
Located within minutes of South Geelong Station, Garden St Café precinct, Eastern Gardens and the Waterfront, this home offers an easy lifestyle in close proximity to local attractions and amenities.
So much to love, so little to do! Just move in and enjoy this gorgeous home in a fabulous location.

Description:
Character Period Home in A Quiet Tree Lined Street
Enviably situated on the high side of a quiet tree lined street is this elegant weatherboard home with a flexible floorplan and functional living.
Step inside and be captivated by the homes period features with a gracious formal living room with ornate fireplace and a separate and flexible family room/meal area featuring a glorious atrium roof with plantation shutters. The kitchen is practical and overlooks the family living and offers a large 900mm oven, dishwasher and stone bench tops.
The master bedroom is located at the front of the house and features a glorious window seat and elegant ensuite with double basins. There are three other good-sized bedrooms two with built in robes, a separate laundry and split system heating and cooling.
Outdoor living is beautifully catered for with a large undercover alfresco area with café blinds to extend its seasons of use. There is a spacious landscaped rear yard with an area for the kids and dog to play and even a spot for the chooks. The home also has rear lane way access with a large double garage with remote access and a separate garden shed all on a large allotment of 700m2.
This beautiful home offers a sublime lifestyle perfectly positioned in a quiet tree lined street in East Geelong, walking distance to the Garden Street shopping precinct and Eastern Gardens. Only a few minutes' drive to the Centre of Geelong and easy access to the Bellarine Peninsula for lazy Sundays at some of the Bellarine's finest restaurants, wineries and cafes.

Description:
ENTERTAINERS PARADISE
This wonderfully bright and spacious brick veneer 4 bed, 2 bath and 3 living family home situated on 665m2 block in a quiet court of only 7 homes, is definitely one to inspect.
This solid family home set in established St Albans Park Homestead estate comprises of spacious front formal living room with double dressed blinds and a bright master suite featuring ceiling fan, WIR, ensuite with corner shower, toilet and IXL heat lamps for those chilly mornings.
Following the wide hallway down, to find a further 3 bedrooms, all with BIR, block out blinds and new carpets.
The central bathroom is light filled and offers sunken bath, separate shower and vanity storage.
Located at the rear of the home you find the lovely open plan living/dining/kitchen area. The carpeted living room offers blockout blinds, Samsung Split system AC and a lovely garden outlook. The dining space easily seats 10 - 12 and is positioned directly off the updated kitchen which offers breakfast bar, AEG Pyrolytic self-cleaning oven, Induction cooktop and brand new dishwasher.
What sets this home apart from the rest, is the wonderful 3rd living indoor/outdoor room offering 42m2 of brilliant entertaining.
Finished off with Merbau deck flooring, blockout blinds, Fujitsu reverse cycle split system and wide stacker doors leading to the fully landscaped rear yard. This room would make an ideal games room or all year round Entertainers paradise!
Outside you will find a rear grassed yard, private established gardens with underground sprinkler system in place. There is also a side plant atrium space on one side and a garden shed on the other. The oversized DLUG also offers a push through rollerdoor ideal for your campervan or trailer.
This fabulous home is located in a quiet court and is a short drive to sporting grounds, Buckleys entertainment complex, 2km to East Geelong cafes precinct and 15 minutes to the nearest coast.

Address: 289 Boundary Road St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
Affordable, Renovated Classic!
Conveniently located close to local schools, shops and public transport, this immaculately renovated 3BR home is the perfect option for the savvy investor or long term 1st home buyer. Currently tenanted with a strong return, the opportunity is there to secure your piece of the popular Geelong real estate market now for the future.
A neat, low maintenance garden borders the classic front facade and driveway leading to a large single carport with roller door which then leads through to a secure brick garage/work shop and expansive undercover alfresco area.
Upon entry you are met with a sense of space and natural light, with a clean palette and stunning original floorboards. From the front foyer is the generous master bedroom featuring large built-in robes and ceiling fan. Along the hallway youll find a good sized 2nd bedroom with built in robe and a 3rd bedroom, both with ceiling fans. There is a smart renovated central bathroom with bath, shower & vanity, a separate toilet and a functional laundry with an abundance of storage.
The light filled main living area features a gas log fire and wall mounted AC, this then leads into the renovated dining & kitchen area featuring tiled floor, classic white cupboards with modern splash back, gas cook-top, oven, range-hood and dishwasher.
At the rear of the home is a large under cover al fresco area perfect for those who love to entertain all year round, along with a spacious, low-maintenance yard with water tank.
With additional features such as gas ducted floor heating, down lights throughout, an abundance of storage & plenty of natural light this home will definitely impress on first inspection.
